channel.title: My page can't be visited via ip or domain
channel.description:
*EDIT* NOTICE: I HAVE FIXED IT */EDIT\*
Hello! My page can't be visited via ip or domain.
I've portforwarded 80 TCP and UDP on my router and firewall. But when I type in my IP in the address bar, it won't load the page. I checked the apache on WampServer, and it says port 80 is working. I'm sure the external IP match with the portforward. So what is the problem?

item.title: My page can't be visited via ip or domain
item.dc:creator: @chrham2 chrham2
item.description:
@chrham2 wrote:

[quote=“runescape3dude, post:7, topic:287726”][quote author=chrham2 link=topic=380394.msg2859825#msg2859825 date=1247093639]
I can by 127.0.0.1, I could do it via IP before, and I still have the same router, it just stopped working.
[/quote]
Are you sure you portforwarded to the right local ip? Are you sure your external IP has not changed?[/quote]
yes[br][br][size=1]Posted on: July 09, 2009, 09:00:43 am[/size][hr]It worked before, but it just stopped working, so it allows port 80.
